      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions - Improvements to consider] Line 190: The RTT baseline is fixed from the first five samples and is never reset or adapted. If the call starts on a high-latency path, or the route changes mid-call, the controller can permanently under-detect or over-detect RTT congestion. Consider using a rolling minimum/slow EWMA baseline or resetting the baseline after a long stable period.\n```suggestion\n// Example direction: track the minimum observed RTT slowly instead of freezing the first samples.\nif (rttMs \u003e 0.0f)\n    baselineRtt_ \u003d baselineRtt_ \u003d\u003d 0.0f ? rttMs : std::min(baselineRtt_, rttMs);\n```",
