      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions - Improvements to consider] Line 660: `setNewBitrate()` is called immediately after `onRembFeedback()` even when the REMB signal does not change the controller target. Because `setNewBitrate()` now refreshes `lastMediaRestart_` only when the bitrate changes this is mostly harmless for equal values, but it still re-enters the bitrate path on every REMB packet and can race with RR-driven updates. Gate the call on an actual bitrate change so only real controller decisions restart/sync the encoder path.\n```suggestion\n            auto newBitrate \u003d bwController_.onRembFeedback(isOveruse);\n            if (newBitrate !\u003d videoBitrateInfo_.videoBitrateCurrent)\n                setNewBitrate(newBitrate);\n```",
